00:32:54.940 --> 00:32:56.200
or is it just a learned habit?

00:32:56.200 --> 00:32:57.295
GARY CATONA: Are you
talking about pitch range?

00:32:57.295 --> 00:32:58.370
AUDIENCE: Yes.

00:32:58.370 --> 00:32:59.780
GARY CATONA: Your
pitch, when you

00:32:59.780 --> 00:33:03.480
change pitch, your vocal cords
change length like a string.

00:33:03.480 --> 00:33:05.790
The higher you go, the
longer the cords become.

00:33:05.790 --> 00:33:08.520
What controls that
movement are muscles.

00:33:08.520 --> 00:33:10.990
So again, it stands to
reason that if you exercise

00:33:10.990 --> 00:33:14.250
those muscles, what
happens to that range?

00:33:14.250 --> 00:33:18.170
[SINGING WITH RISING PITCH]

00:33:18.170 --> 00:33:19.320
It goes up.

00:33:19.320 --> 00:33:22.960
So the proper exercise will
definitely increase and improve

00:33:22.960 --> 00:33:24.941
your pitch ability.

00:33:24.941 --> 00:33:27.440
AUDIENCE: So it sounds like a
common theme is approaching it

00:33:27.440 --> 00:33:27.980
as a muscle.

00:33:27.980 --> 00:33:28.980
GARY CATONA: Absolutely.

00:33:28.980 --> 00:33:31.021
MALE SPEAKER: And most
people, through the years,

00:33:31.021 --> 00:33:33.120
have experienced
some form of atrophy,

00:33:33.120 --> 00:33:34.997
in that they haven't
exercised that range,

00:33:34.997 --> 00:33:37.330
and it becomes smaller as you
get older just because you

00:33:37.330 --> 00:33:38.710
don't--

00:33:38.710 --> 00:33:41.250
GARY CATONA: Singing is an
art form, but the basis of it

00:33:41.250 --> 00:33:42.890
is science.

00:33:42.890 --> 00:33:46.000
And there are two different
dimensions that people confuse.

00:33:46.000 --> 00:33:48.990
They try to make the teaching of
singing into too much of an art

00:33:48.990 --> 00:33:50.750
form and not enough
of a science.

00:33:50.750 --> 00:33:51.880
Do you see what I'm saying?

00:33:51.880 --> 00:33:55.320
So if I feel as though
the sound's coming

00:33:55.320 --> 00:33:57.740
from inside my head,
it doesn't mean

00:33:57.740 --> 00:34:01.510
you teach that because that's
physiologically impossible.

00:34:01.510 --> 00:34:04.160
It means you teach it
properly, and then you

00:34:04.160 --> 00:34:06.470
deal with the artistic
dimension in a different way.

00:34:06.470 --> 00:34:09.659
But most teachers don't
understand that distinction.

00:34:09.659 --> 00:34:11.437
So again, think
of it as a sport.

00:34:11.437 --> 00:34:12.770
When you sing, you're an artist.

00:34:12.770 --> 00:34:16.949
But as a student,
you're a voice builder.

00:34:16.949 --> 00:34:20.920
AUDIENCE: I talk with a
very low tone of voice,

00:34:20.920 --> 00:34:25.389
but I would like to make it
higher because I keep getting

00:34:25.389 --> 00:34:30.330
