00:34:39.500 --> 00:34:44.870
Don't try to monkey with
what nature has given you

00:34:44.870 --> 00:34:47.250
to the extent that you ruin
something that's natural.

00:34:47.250 --> 00:34:48.633
You have a naturally low voice.

00:34:48.633 --> 00:34:50.799
I would enjoy it and just
try to-- I would encourage

00:34:50.799 --> 00:34:53.422
you to build your
voice at this level.

00:34:53.422 --> 00:34:55.130
And you'll see, your
range will increase.

00:34:55.130 --> 00:34:56.980
But in terms of raising
your speaking voice,

00:34:56.980 --> 00:34:58.438
I don't recommend
that you do that.

00:34:58.438 --> 00:35:00.320
AUDIENCE: But I sing
with a very high pitch.

00:35:00.320 --> 00:35:02.260
I can sing high
pitch [INAUDIBLE].

00:35:02.260 --> 00:35:04.010
GARY CATONA: I'd have
to hear your singing

00:35:04.010 --> 00:35:07.530
to make a thorough
judgment about that.

00:35:07.530 --> 00:35:09.780
MALE SPEAKER: I think studies
have shown, though, too,

00:35:09.780 --> 00:35:11.980
that the deeper your voice,
the more authoritative,

00:35:11.980 --> 00:35:13.980
whether you're in a meeting
or doing a newscast.

00:35:13.980 --> 00:35:14.938
GARY CATONA: Of course.

00:35:14.938 --> 00:35:17.910
The voice is a highly
psychological aspect

00:35:17.910 --> 00:35:19.380
of who we are.

00:35:19.380 --> 00:35:22.030
It gives us power.

00:35:22.030 --> 00:35:25.130
AUDIENCE: How to project better,
make one's voice lower, slower,

00:35:25.130 --> 00:35:27.900
and cut out ums.

00:35:27.900 --> 00:35:30.160
GARY CATONA: Again, singing,
your vocal mechanism is,

00:35:30.160 --> 00:35:31.070
think of it like a muscle.

00:35:31.070 --> 00:35:32.880
You have to improve the
ability of your vocal muscle

00:35:32.880 --> 00:35:33.970
to create vowel sounds.

00:35:33.970 --> 00:35:38.120
If I go [SINGING] hee,
you're hearing an E vowel.

00:35:38.120 --> 00:35:40.980
You're hearing my throat
making that sound.

00:35:40.980 --> 00:35:42.480
You have to develop
that capability.

00:35:42.480 --> 00:35:43.620
Speaking is basically that.

00:35:43.620 --> 00:35:45.010
It's flexing muscles.

00:35:45.010 --> 00:35:47.260
So by using the proper
voice building exercises,

00:35:47.260 --> 00:35:50.050
you develop the ability to flex
your muscles more efficiently

00:35:50.050 --> 00:35:52.750
and more effectively, and
you produce more voice.

00:35:52.750 --> 00:35:57.000
So volume in voice is greater
pressure below the vocal folds.

00:35:57.000 --> 00:35:59.510
When you speak or sing,
the cords come together,

00:35:59.510 --> 00:36:01.530
and the breath that
normally flies through

00:36:01.530 --> 00:36:02.940
is stopped to some extent.

00:36:02.940 --> 00:36:05.770
And that pressure is the
source of your voice.

00:36:05.770 --> 00:36:08.590
The greater the pressure,
the more voice you have.

00:36:08.590 --> 00:36:10.680
So by building
the vocal muscles,

00:36:10.680 --> 00:36:12.850
to vocal cords come
together more strongly,

00:36:12.850 --> 00:36:15.720
which prevents more
breath from escaping,

00:36:15.720 --> 00:36:17.442
which increases the
sound of your voice.

00:36:17.442 --> 00:36:19.150
AUDIENCE: Would you
